# enclave-sign-sdk standards

- Document signing crypto only — no app UI, storage backends, or API handlers.
- Import `@enclave/pqc-primitives` for all cryptography; never import `@noble/*` directly.
- One folder per concern: `envelope/`, `decrypt/`, `keys/`, `tokens/`, `signature/`, `manifest/`.
- Manifest canonicalization lives in `manifest/` and is shared by encrypt + verify paths.
- Validate inputs at public API boundaries.
- Tests live in `tests/`, not under `src/`.
- Top-level shim files (`envelope-crypto.ts`, etc.) exist for Deno vendor paths — do not add logic there.
